subject: p16055653
Impression: Both lung volumes are very low. Right lower lung consolidation concerning for pneumonia, new since, is unchanged. Apparent cardiomegaly, prominent pulmonary vasculature and azygous vein and widened mediastinal contour may be due to very low lung volumes and supine position of patient. There is no pneumothorax or pleural effusion. Right PICC line ends at mid-to-lower SVC.
